The paper discusses the design of autonomous robots and their perception of space, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The paper also discusses the need for robots to develop their own way of perceiving, which involves artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of a retina and sensorimotor data to learn spatial configuration involves computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper discusses the use of invariants in sensorimotor laws, which is a concept commonly used in neural networks (cs.NE).
